refuse to chase PM copy wallets when they are paying nosebleed prices on tiny windows. That matters heading into 19h because our bot\u2019s YES entries should come from genuine edge, not from copying already-priced microstructure.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep treating **HL major-coin consensus as the higher-order directional prior**.\n- Add a practical copy-intel caution for PM execution: **when top PM wallet flow is mixed and average copy price is above ~0.65, treat it as crowded microstructure, not alpha.**\n- I am not changing live code yet, but this should inform the next smart-entry pass, especially around evening overpricing.\n\n**Next:** Backtest whether PM trades entered when copy-wallet average price is above 0.65 underperform lower-priced windows. If yes, promote a new anti-crowding filter for evening sessions.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 18:30 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Liquidation Signal Coverage Is Too Sparse for Live PM Scoring\n\n**Task:** Test whether the liquidation detector can already serve as a useful alpha input for PM trade selection",
